The paper deals with the capacity region of a communication channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channel considered is a multiple access channel (MAC), which is a type of network communication protocol (cs.NI). The channel has feedback, which is a common feature in communication systems and can be modeled using control theory (cs.SI). The paper also discusses inner and outer bounds, which are techniques used in optimization and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper provides explicit conclusions for specific scenarios, which is a common theme in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
